The federal government has been taken to court by detained Deputy Commissioner of Police, DCP Abba Kyari.  He took FG to court to the Federal High Court in Abuja challenging his continued detention by the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), according to DailyPost. In the suit marked FHC/ABJ/CS/182/22, Kyari who is currently on suspension from the Nigerian Police Force is seeking an order of court to immediately release him. In the alternative, the suspended DCP, being held by the NDLEA over his alleged involvement in hard drug trafficking wants the court to admit him to bail in liberal conditions. Justice Inyang Eden Ekwo is expected to take the ex-parte application filed along with the suit any moment today. Details later.  source Daily Post reports that Ohanaeze Ndigbo worldwide has urged the Federal Government of Nigeria to allow the suspended head of IRT, DCP Abba Kyari, to be extradited to the United States to face the allegations from the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) over the hushpuppi scandal. Recall that the FBI… In "News" •Embattled suspended DCP Abba Kyari ABUJA - The suspended Head of the Intelligence Response Team, DCP Abba Kyari, has been arrested by the Nigerian police. It was gathered that he was arrested alongside four others on Monday. Kyari was arrested hours after National Drug Law Enforcement Agency declared him wanted… In "Top Stories" •Suspended DCP Abba Kyari ABUJA - The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), has declared the suspended head of the Police Intelligence Response Team (IRT), DCP Abba Kyari, wanted over alleged drug offences. NDLEA spokesperson Femi Babafemi made the announcement during a press conference in Abuja on Monday. He said… In "Top Stories"